{{ infobox person | name = Louis Leprince-Ringuet | birth_date = {{birth date|1901|3|27|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Alès]], [[France]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2000|12|23|1901|3|27|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Paris]], France | nationality = [[France|French]] | occupation = [[Physicist]] | alma_mater = [[École Polytechnique]] | known for = Member of the [[Académie française]] }}
'''Louis Leprince-Ringuet''' (27 March 1901, [[Alès]] &ndash; 23 December 2000, [[Paris]]) was a [[France|French]] physicist, [[telecommunications]] engineer, essayist and historian of science.<ref>{{cite journal|author=Jacob, Maurice|title=Obituary: Louis Leprince-Ringuet|journal=Physics Today|date=July 2001|volume=54|issue=7|pages=78–79|url=http://scitation.aip.org/content/aip/magazine/physicstoday/article/54/7/10.1063/1.1397405|doi=10.1063/1.1397405|bibcode=2001PhT....54g..78J}}</ref>
