{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}} '''National Astronaut Day''' is an American [[commemorative day]] held on May 5 since 2017.<ref name="Space.com article">{{cite web|last1=Wall|first1=Mike|title=Happy National Astronaut Day!|url=https://www.space.com/36725-national-astronaut-day-2017-uniphi-facebook-live.html|website=Space.com|accessdate=May 6, 2018}}</ref> It commemorates the first United States [[human spaceflight]], on May 5, 1961, piloted by [[astronaut]] [[Alan Shepard]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.techtimes.com/articles/226990/20180505/national-astronaut-day-commemorates-launch-of-first-american-in-space.htm |title=National Astronaut Day Commemorates Launch of First American in Space |publisher=Tech Times |date=May 5, 2018 |accessdate=2018-05-07}}</ref>
