{{Infobox UN resolution |number = 259 |organ = SC |date = September 27 |year = 1968 |meeting = 1454 |code = S/RES/259 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/259(1968) |for = 12 |abstention = 3 |against = 0 |subject = The situation in the Middle East |result = Adopted |image = |caption = }}
'''[[United Nations]] [[List of UN Security Council Resolutions|Security Council Resolution]] 259''', adopted on September 27, 1968, concerned with the welfare of the inhabitants of the [[Israeli-occupied territories|Arab territories then occupied by Israel]] after the [[Six-Day War]], the Council requested the [[United Nations Secretary-General|Secretary-General]] send a [[Special Representative of the Secretary-General|Special Representative]] to report on the implementation of [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 237|resolution 237]]. The Council requested that [[Israel]] receive and co-operate with the Special Representative and that the Secretary-General should be afforded all co-operation in order to implement the present resolution.
The resolution was passed with 12 votes to none; [[Canada]], [[Denmark]] and the [[United States]] abstained.
